node.text: In honor of Colon Cancer Awareness month, I am partnering with @letsgetchecked and @colorectalcanceralliance to donate $1M worth of their life saving Colon Cancer Screening Tests to underserved communities as well as $100,000 to fuel critical research.  Colon Cancer is easily undetectable, these kits makes it easy to test yourself early, which is the best method for overcoming this life-threatening disease.  Visit www.letsgetchecked.com for more information.  #Ad #letsgetchecked

node.text:
I am so thrilled to have gotten the opportunity to speak with the students in the @adidas S.E.E.D program based out of the Brooklyn Creator Farm in NYC. 

S.E.E.D. is two-year hands on  program strategically created to welcome new talent into the design pipeline. 

Thank you to @adidasNYC and @adidasLA for arranging this inspiring conversation. So excited to work with these talented women in the future. 

Learn more at adidas.com/us/zoe_saldana

Las Noticias is made in partnership with Dos Rayas Productions. 

You can donate to Nicolas Chavez’s family at the following link: https://www.gofundme.com/f/rest-in-paradise-nicolas-chavez

Not knowing how our families are doing and having to see videos and photos of our people being beaten and taken away by the government to join the military against their will.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Zoe Saldana on July 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Lend your voice to the fight Amplify Cuban voices by asking about and listening to our stories, experiences, and troubles. As an ally, you should lend your voice to help get the Cuban people's voices heard in your circles to continue educating people who may not have a lot of knowledge on the topic. Ask your Cuban friends questions about why this is happening, share their stories on your platforms and don't ignore something that is happening 90 miles from the U.S. coastline.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Zoe Saldana on July 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Spread Awareness Sharing news, photos, and videos of what is happening on the island is the best way to spread awareness. Cuban's are at the forefront of what is happening and they are one of the best primary sources to listen to since the Cuban government does not want the world to know what they are doing to their people. Here are some pages sharing constant coverage, sharing ways to donate, and protests to attend: @americavaldess @revolucioncuba @mimaincuba @adncuba @studentsforafreecuba @cubanospalente'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Zoe Saldana on July 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Help in anyway you can Share, donate, attend a protest, find out how you can help the Cuban people in their fight for freedom. Whether it be donating $1 to benefit a mutual aid fund, sharing a post, or adding data to a phone plan so Cuban's can contact their family and friends abroad, the help is appreciated! @laura__marrero -Laura is receiving funds and medicine donations in Miami to send to Cuba. @cubanospalante -they are collecting funds through Zelle at cubanospalante@gmail.com.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Zoe Saldana on June 21, 2021 tagging @jaredlehr, @makeupbyvera7, @cissaldana, @dagobertogalan, @marsalwebb, @asaliasaldana, and @pirateyadimar. May be a closeup of 1 person.

node.text: Here’s to 43 years around the sun, to making yourself the joke for the sake of those you love, to not being the favorite sometimes, to failed selfie attempts, to sleepless nights not feeling good enough, to not caring in my 40’s about half the things I cared for in my 30’s, to saying I love you when I’m mad, to asking for forgiveness when I screw up, to caring a whole lot for other people’s children besides my own, to practicing love instead of being a lazy ass at it, to being scared of dying, to figuring it out only after I’ve fucked it up multiple times over. Here’s to actively listening to others, especially my children, to loving and respecting my parents, to smiling long enough to feel it, to saying no, to saying yes. Here’s to one more year I get to be grateful to be here. Thank you for all the love and birthday wishes.
